commit_message:
VMware: fix bug with booting from volume

When booting from volume ensure that the volume is on the same
datastore as the instance being booted.

Fixes bug 1223709

Change-Id: Iddb70cdd7e358c401ef4f0b4d9e66b9655c2feeb

commit_message:
Install bridge-utils only if needed

The package bridge-utils is useful only if we have nova-network.
If we use Quantum, we don't have to install it.

This patch provides a condition "quantum_enabled" to check before the
installation of the package.

*Note* I replaced neutron with quantum because neutron does not exists.

Fix bug #1176087

Change-Id: Iee2ecbf2023ab211d67cb9bfeb3dbc5b4bb3eb89
Signed-off-by: Paul Belanger <paul.belanger@polybeacon.com>

commit_message:
Disallow access/modify members of deleted image

It should not be possible to access or modify memberships for a
deleted image. A 404 error will now be returned if a deleted
images' members are accessed or modified.

Fixes: bug #1207266
Co-authored-by: Hirofumi Ichihara <ichihara.hirofumi@lab.ntt.co.jp>

Change-Id: I3e1a7c1cd96b8c85cf0c20286533ced510580492

commit_message:
Fix several flake8 issues in the plugins/xenserver code

Due to some issues in the gate, several flake8 errors got merged
recently. This patch fixes the most recent issues found.

For the H304 relative import errors, we have to skip those because they
are put into /etc/xensource/scripts which is the current working
directory when running the plugin.

For the H231 incompatible python 3 'except x,y' construct, we have to
skip those because this code is written to run on python 2.4 and 'except
x as y' does not work with python 2.4.

Note that in cleaning up some of the H304 failures for relative imports,
I also re-arranged the imports to follow the hacking guide of doing
standard library packages first, then third party packages, and finally
nova-specific packages.

Closes-Bug: #1229753

Change-Id: I1c2211fd6a10d43d7e65cdb4e18530397788cf2c

[{'created': '2013-09-20 15:16:22.000000000', 'message': 'Bring up interface when enslaving to a bridge

Right now, if the interface to be used for a nova-network bridge is
not already up, nova-network will enslave it and leave it down,
which is not very helpful. Since an interface for this purpose is
likely to be left unconfigured by the base OS, expecting it to be
up is not ideal.

commit_message:
Bring up interface when enslaving to a bridge

Right now, if the interface to be used for a nova-network bridge is
not already up, nova-network will enslave it and leave it down,
which is not very helpful. Since an interface for this purpose is
likely to be left unconfigured by the base OS, expecting it to be
up is not ideal.

Change-Id: I14564c0bcb55b9dd427ccaa8fb217e38121d4b71
Closes-bug: 1228183

commit_message:
Format error on urlfetch.get fail

The error messages for fetch failures of nested stacks have too much
detail. This change formats fetch fail errors in the same way
that TemplateResource does.

Change-Id: Ib8afa281a53f895086ce8890c828fe4a8bb469ae
Closes-Bug: #1214227

commit_message:
Fix volume_rpcapi calls for chance/simple scheds

Change the chance and simple schedulers to pass the snapshot_id and
image_id parameters correctly volume_rpcapi, so that their values reach
cinder-volume.

Change-Id: I0abbca1fa0445c5233387a0f17363fc092d39b88
Closes-Bug: #1212710

Graph visualiztion  is useful feature, but I'm concerted about extra dependencies, especially since pydot does not seem to be python 3 compatible (well, at least 'pip install pydot' failed in my py3 virtualenv), and requires old version of pyparsing.

Maybe it is better to provide an instruction (want to draw a graph? install this or that and run this 3 lines of code), and do not add any code to taskflow.

Of course, there might be some useful improvements that will make graph look better: nice captions on edges and good __str__ methods for nodes, for example."}, {'account_id': 7349, 'date': '2013-09-24 11:58:21.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 6.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-09-24 11:59:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Works for me

commit_message:
Add Nova Cells support

Bring nova-cells support into puppet-nova.

Cells is a feature introduced in Grizzly and improved in Havana.
This patch configures nodes to be part of a parent or child
cell.

It also adds "it_configures" in spec_helper.

Work in progress: do not merge.

Implements: blueprint cells-support
Change-Id: I10b6a0080cfbefeddf6a19fc661a3ddfaf3da218
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

commit_message:
User and Database List in Create Not Validated

Fix #1: Every database in instance.users.databases should exist in
instance.databases, otherwise the guest will attempt to grant
privileges to a database that can't possibly exist.

Fix #2: The (name, host) of each user in instance.users should be
unique, otherwise there is a semantic duplicate.

Note: instance.users.databases is already checked for uniqueness via
apischema's uniqueItems assertion.

Change-Id: Ib0a148a1d7dcf6adf2a899b15db815273e5688a4
Closes-Bug: #1219627

commit_message:
show limit summary in GB

Prior this change RAM in limit overview would be shown in MB,
but it makes sense to change this to use variable sizes.
This change also introduces to show 1 decimal position for sizes
shown in float (earlier it was zero).

Fixes bug 1223856

Change-Id: I243c9ea1616bc2684911b5d7d9399b4c3ee4aacd

commit_message:
Make tenant name lookup for keystone user lazy

Previously, when you managed a keystone user, Puppet
would start by loading all information available
about each user. Most of this information was loaded
with a single call to user-list, but the tenant name
required an additional two commands (one to get the
tenantId, and an additional one to get the tenant name)

This patch makes the tenant lookup lazy, meaning that
those additional calls will only be performed when
the tenant attribute is actually used. This will
cause a significant performance increase for the
case where only a large set of users exists, and
only a small fraction of them need to be managed.

Partial-Bug: 1224179
Change-Id: I7141d8e922005ecae33c2c596c9806a03fede53f

commit_message:
Specific /usr/local/bin/hus-cmd rootwrap filter

Add a specific filter for /usr/local/bin/hus-cmd, rather than adding
/usr/local/bin to the list of exec_path in rootwrap.conf. This allows to
sync rootwrap directly from oslo-incubator without having to edit the
default value for exec_dirs.

Change-Id: Ic264ca248d025fb5496fe0b48e8b3ec9376fb9e2

commit_message:
Test the response body when deleting a alarm

This change test the response body when deleting a alarm.

Because since wsme>=0.5b5 , the return code and the response
are the those expected by ceilometer.

Fixes bug #1209093

Change-Id: I6699665be5938a9c699b179d241725b242bbea4a

This is needed to ensure that when using run_tests.sh requirements
are handled correctly. Both requirements.txt and test-requirements.txt
need to be handed to pip at the same time to ensure that all
dependencies are satisfied and we don't upgrade a package to be
outside of the version constraints set by requirements.txt when
installing dependencies for the packages in test-requirements.txt.

Change-Id: I89bcf4e44b7274dca535e8e1d2eeb0adb142cabb

commit_message:
Sync install_venv_common.py from oslo-incubator

This is needed to ensure that when using run_tests.sh requirements
are handled correctly. Both requirements.txt and test-requirements.txt
need to be handed to pip at the same time to ensure that all
dependencies are satisfied and we don't upgrade a package to be
outside of the version constraints set by requirements.txt when
installing dependencies for the packages in test-requirements.txt.

Change-Id: I89bcf4e44b7274dca535e8e1d2eeb0adb142cabb

commit_message:
Fixes file mode bits of compute/manager.py

Modified file permission from 755 to 644.
Removed a redundant blank line to avoid merged errors in gerrit
which happens if no content has changed.

Partially fixes bug #1224226

Change-Id: Ia300ac05fbeb251bb801cec44011df94ce8f16b0

commit_message:
change pyparsing to >= 2.0.1

cliff 1.4.5 was released and bumped pyparsing min to >= 2.0, which
is beyond global requirements. This has wedged all of the gate,
and no changes will flow until we address this.

Change-Id: I9cfae4bb57f3b9e154d8f044fd36d795e42f7de3

commit_message:
Fail tests early if mongod is not found

Instead of letting the tests report connection errors,
check for the mongod process early and don't run the
tests at all if it is not found.

Change-Id: Iebf420ba62954ffe0d2b9c23375c9a0ff9673845

After discussing this with Flavio, I feel more comfortable approving this patch at this time.

My concern is that the method for declaring the operation to use is too heavyweight and magical, and doesn't take enough advantage of the facilities exposed by the Python interpreter (e.g., default args, optional args, required args [argument handling], and function mapping).

I'd love to see a method that takes advantage of the upcoming enum feature (https://pypi.python.org/pypi/enum34/), and/or uses interface-oriented programming + base controller classes and uses late-binding to determine which instance to use.

Classes like: ZmqClient, HttpClient, etc.

Method look up like: {[enum] operations.queues: base.queues}, and then fail an operation with a TypeError if passing in the arguments to the method looked up fails.

Just some thoughts - I'm sure it'll all be refined after some use and experimentation! :)

Thanks for your efforts!"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-09-24 16:20:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: No score

commit_message:
This adds a transport layer request spec class

The idea here is to be declarative i.e. specify *what* is desired.
It's up to the respective transport (e.g. http, zmq etc.) to turn a
request spec into an appropriate request.

The request spec class also performs some basic validation.  The
assumption is that the Marconi API is stable and known for a given
version. The API info for version 1 is thus captured in the code and
not read from the home document.

Nevertheless I have introduced a separate api_info() function that
allows us to source the API info from the home document at a later point.

Please note also that the `request.Spec` has a `headers` dict property
that can be used by the auth layer to inject auth tokens etc.

Change-Id: Ia72bfadcc84e7aba69aa5f32d76dfa0dc1083e0d

commit_message:
Refactor client's structure to reflect Marconi's

This patch moves the transport package under queues.

Implements blueprint change-marconi-structure

Change-Id: Ib4e22bece449ea689a16cf3b8ce427efed580d69

subject: Use built-in print() instead of print statement

commit_message:
Use built-in print() instead of print statement

In python 3 print statement is not supported, so we should use
only print() functions.

Fixes bug 1226943

Change-Id: I206fe870eea21522e28318b9cfa062239e54c391

commit_message:
Ensure prop protections are read/enforced in order

Property protections need to be enforced in the order specified by the
configuration file. i.e. [^x_owner.*] should be enforced before [.*]
given the example config.

To achieve this, use a list of tuples to store the rules rather than a
dict, and also ensure to specify dict_type when parsing the
configuration file for python 2.6.

Fixes bug 1224449

Change-Id: Ib22cb34b7daef081c95717b55a991b8d613468c4

commit_message:
Remove unused utility classes

Removing ThreadGroupExecutor allows to get rid of threading2
dependency. LastFedIter is also not used, so there is no
reason to keep it.

Change-Id: Id396ab59ebf1e2314ef620417d7cac09e1ab8d3b

commit_message:
Add config files

Config files needed to be manually provided.
Project-info files contain generic information about the project
or release
repos-map is a mapping between git and launchpad repositories
viz_cfg is the configuration file for the Envision viz

Change-Id: Iacbac888a5a5baec2f0d6c2c24d84a42b9391204

commit_message:
cap cliff to < 1.4.5

cliff 1.4.5 bumped it's requirement of pyparsing to > 2 in a
patch release. This wedge the gate.

Uncapping pyparsing is probably the right long term thing to do,
however the infra mirror takes time to bring in new requirements.
So be more expedited and use cliff < 1.4.5 instead.

Gratuitous change to takeit out of the gate

Change-Id: Ifd799bfd99862753bd6e3cb1745bd6dc7e329f7f

commit_message:
Remove mox from test-requirements.txt

mox is a test requirement, but isn't being used. mock was recently named
the chosen mocking library, and it's already in use here in
marconiclient.

Change-Id: I24a73d57ad0ccac29db317e0f4e72efdeb8962d8

commit_message:
cliff 1.4.5 workaround

cliff 1.4.5 doesn't work with stable/grizzly python toolchain, to
short circuit this, force installing a compatible cliff before we
kick off the whole process, that will at least let us limp along
until we can get a better resolution.

Change-Id: If3a2602031943a0710882f5e1e37ef9e0bc4392e

commit_message:
Backup for shared folders info implemented

Allow access to share functionality added rules to exportfs on
the fly but this data was missed after restart. This path
implements functionality that store generic rules from
/var/lib/nfs/etab to /etc/exports

Change-Id: I4611f89084d0ec661d82338f46c5f71f77b36fb2

commit_message:
Replace decprecated method aliases in tests

Some of the TestCase methods have been deprecated since python 2.7.
We need use correct names.

http://docs.python.org/2/library/unittest.html#deprecated-aliases

  * replace 'assert_' with 'assertTrue'
  * replace 'failIf' with 'assertFalse'
  * replace 'failUnlessAlmostEqual' with 'assertAlmostEqual'

Change-Id: If9f24b8e944b980b1c767efda7c5244fcf8c5cae

commit_message:
This adds a transport layer request spec class

The idea here is to be declarative i.e. specify *what* is desired.
It's up to the respective transport (e.g. http, zmq etc.) to turn a
request spec into an appropriate request.

The request spec class also performs some basic validation. The
assumption is that the Marconi API is stable and known for a given
version. The API info for version 1 is thus captured in the code and
not read from the home document.
Nevertheless I have introduced a separate `api.info()` function that
allows us to source the API info from the home document at a later point.

Please note also that the `request.Spec` has a `headers` dict property
that can be used by the auth layer to inject auth tokens etc.

This branch fixes most of the issues found during the review of
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/47538/

Change-Id: If00e359e0aca7b78a6256cacf7e0caf294f6bb91

commit_message:
Adds a hus local filter in volume.filters

Everytime rootwrap gets synced from Oslo, etc/cinder/rootwrap.conf gets
synced likewise. There for it is best to add a specific filter to
volume.filters rather than editing rootwrap.conf directly
This patch adds a filter to handle the local case of the HUS command.

Change-Id: I690b49d213b17dbb4edf444058a1b3af100118b5

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-09-20 14:04:33.000000000', 'message': 'Fix HOT parser constraint translation

There is currently a fundamental mismatch between the output from
the HOT parser constraint translation, and the actual schema supported
by the ParamSchema in parameters.py

The main mismatch is the description field, which should not be provided
as a tuple with the constraint, but via the "ConstraintDescription"
field, which is common to all contraints (not one description per
constraint as currently specified in the HOT specification and code)

This modifies the HOT parser interface, but until we decouple the
Parameters impelementation from the CFN schema, I don't think we
have any alternative.

Change-Id: Ie9278068068b1e7feedb70477651b03816e4a5c9
Closes-Bug: #1224111

commit_message:
Fix HOT parser constraint translation

There is currently a fundamental mismatch between the output from
the HOT parser constraint translation, and the actual schema supported
by the ParamSchema in parameters.py

The main mismatch is the description field, which should not be provided
as a tuple with the constraint, but via the "ConstraintDescription"
field, which is common to all contraints (not one description per
constraint as currently specified in the HOT specification and code)

This modifies the HOT parser interface, but until we decouple the
Parameters impelementation from the CFN schema, I don't think we
have any alternative.

Change-Id: Ie9278068068b1e7feedb70477651b03816e4a5c9
Closes-Bug: #1224111

[{'created': '2013-09-23 08:48:05.000000000', 'message': 'Reduce image_list_detailed calls

When showing a form of launching an instance, image_list_detailed is called twice.
populate_image_id_choices and populate_instance_snapshot_id_choices both call
get_available_images(). get_available_images() supports the cache of image list
and it is better to share the cache by both methods.

Closes-Bug: #1229080

Fixes a bug that utils.get_available_images() raises a traceback
when image_list for a project raises an exception.

Closes-Bug: #1229083

commit_message:
Reduce image_list_detailed calls

When showing a form of launching an instance, image_list_detailed is called twice.
populate_image_id_choices and populate_instance_snapshot_id_choices both call
get_available_images(). get_available_images() supports the cache of image list
and it is better to share the cache by both methods.

Closes-Bug: #1229080

Fixes a bug that utils.get_available_images() raises a traceback
when image_list for a project raises an exception.

Closes-Bug: #1229083

Add unittests for images_and_snapshots.utils to cover the above two fixes.

Change-Id: I829a430c84e48de4faf028bdfad74b0cd8f22dc9

commit_message:
GPFS Driver missing clone depth limit for snapshots

GPFS driver is fixed to handle snapshot clones correctly. Previously,
these were allowed to grow without respecting limit defined in config
flag gpfs_max_clone_depth.  This change adds the depth check operation
in create_snapshot.

To ensure that all clone files are cleaned up, the delete_snapshot
method now marks snapshots to be deleted with ts file extension
and attempts to delete the snapshot.  If the snapshot cannot be
deleted because it has clone children, it will be deleted when the
child is deleted.

Closes-Bug: #1227366

Change-Id: I4fb2a720b55dbe033159e6fb341f6e2f1508776e

Refactor PXE DHCP Option support.

The previous support imported pxe into driver, but driver is meant to
be entirely decoupled from specific baremetal drivers.

commit_message:
Drop warning messages from mock/single keymgr's

The current Nova default key manager is conf_key_mgr.

Give that ConfKeyManager extends SingleKeyManager which
extends MockKeyManager and ConfKeyManager it would seem
that we should probably drop the warning about using
the key manager super classes.

As is running Nova with this code would always produce two log
WARNING messages.

configure the maximum amount of objects that can be retrieved by
the aforementioned function.

When using RetrievePropertiesEx the server may allocate resources
in case additional calls are made. These are addressed by reading the
extra resources using ContinueRetrievePropertiesEx (if necessary)
or CancelRetrievePropertiesEx (when the necessary result has been found).

commit_message:
Use RetrievePropertiesEx instead of RetrieveProperties

Fixes bug 1183654

The fix also adds a configuration variable enabling the user to
configure the maximum amount of objects that can be retrieved by
the aforementioned function.

When using RetrievePropertiesEx the server may allocate resources
in case additional calls are made. These are addressed by reading the
extra resources using ContinueRetrievePropertiesEx (if necessary)
or CancelRetrievePropertiesEx (when the necessary result has been found).

DocImpact

(cherry picked from commit e331287cdd1300878bfb9bbb3630889370e5fa72)

Change-Id: Iec799f5c04e21017804711dbdcda1ebd318153f1

Regardless I'm probably ok with it but I am concerned about backward compatability (ie existing Grizzly installs that don't upgrade to Dumpling).  I can be convinced of course but for now I'd need some more explanation.  Especially since there's a half in openstack half in external env variables model that seems to be happening here."}, {'account_id': 6984, 'date': '2013-08-27 13:33:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Well it's more a real patch in the first place since the driver doesn't use 'rbd_user' flag (it's a known bug). While configuring the RBD backend on Grizzly, the operator must hack the upstart script from cinder-volume to use the proper user otherwise the default user (admin) from the CLI will be used. Then this patch provides both a patch for Dumpling and a more natural fix for Grizzly.
The command line options always prioritises against the env variable. Thus if the operator configured the env var with a different user and had set the rbd_user with a different user, this'll break cinder-volume. However the probability is extremely low. 
In the end, please note that the change will work for any Ceph release on Grizzly.

commit_message:
Fix get fsid for Dumpling Ceph CLI

This bug only affects Grizzly since Havana's driver
uses both librbd and librados.
The new ceph CLI from Dumpling doesn't use the "CEPH_ARGS"
environment variable which breaks the 'ceph fsid' command
while trying to create a volume from an image.
the driver doesn't use 'rbd_user' flag (it's a known bug). While
configuring the RBD backend on Grizzly, the operator must hack the
upstart script from cinder-volume to use the proper user otherwise the
default user (admin) from the CLI will be used. Then this patch provides
both a patch for Dumpling and a more natural fix for Grizzly. The
command line options always prioritises against the env variable. Thus
if the operator configured the env var with a different user and had set
the rbd_user with a different user, this'll break cinder-volume.
However the probability is extremely low. In the end, please note
that the change will work for any Ceph release on Grizzly.

Change-Id: Iece29823cc90808e6f7c352754b8a9c8cff84da6
Fixes: bug #1213913

commit_message:
Add delete support for volume type encryption

This modification adds delete support to the volume type
encryption API extension.  The delete operation is not
permitted when the encrypted volume type is in use by an
existing volume.

Change-Id: Ic490fd3f0f1b1282cd24c65886c92beb88d30560
Implements: blueprint encrypt-cinder-volumes

commit_message:
Consider downloading a valid status for CinderVolume

"downloading" should be considered a in-progress state while creating a volume
from an image. Because Cinder will first create a volume with specified size
and set its status to downloading, then start fetching the image from glance
and copying it to the volume.

Fixes bug #1222676

Change-Id: I573440f3184c3d47df0d7e78146b0ed030606d86

commit_message:
Floating ip assignement support

'floating_ip_pool' field added to Node Groups
and Node Group Templates.

'floating_ip_pool' may be Network ID or Floation IP pool name.

If this field is not None then Savanna will:
* create a Floating IP for each instance in the Node Group
* assign it on Cluster start or scaling
* remove it on Cluster Deletion.

Validation added for 'floating_ip_pool' field.

Docs and Sample Configs update

Co-Authored-By: Andrew Lazarev <alazarev@mirantis.com>

Fixes bug: #1186874
Implements blueprint ips-assignment-mechanism

Change-Id: Id7438b533d140916d683e7ca47424aa00b66a1a0

commit_message:
Sync gettextutils from oslo

Some Messages, like those from Invalid exceptions, use a Message within
a Message, and we were only translating the base Message but not the
Message substitution within.

Fixes bug: #1221808

Change-Id: Ic3119df23a090cfaa160c1461e955f0af55fe1cf

Clean up job/jobboard code

In order to start working on the job and
jobboard code we need to tidy it up a little
with comments as to what the intended usage
and functionality of these two components is.

commit_message:
Fix Instance object assumptions about joins

The Instance object was assuming that security_groups and info_cache
were always joined for single instance_get() type queries.  This is a poor
assumption to make.  The object should explicitly ask for info_cache and
security_groups to be included in the DB object when necessary.

Also, we should actually fix sqlalchemy api to not join these always, but
that's probably too large of a change right now.  Instead, make sure we
don't ask to join them twice in the same query.

Fixes bug 1227251

Change-Id: Ib39a3d041904fb5ecebbe152f2fede135a0cdb6f

commit_message:
Instance object incorrectly handles None info_cache

1) When getting records from the DB, it's possible for info_cache to be
None, but this case was ignored.
2) When de-serializing Instance with a None info_cache, a traceback
would occur.

Fixes bug 1228426

Change-Id: I60e610aeafc9dea8d832adec10baaaecbae75215

commit_message:
Don't allow pci_devices/security_groups to be None

These should never be able to be None in the Instance object.  They are
lists and can be empty, however.

Fixes bug 1228402

Change-Id: Id250f8921926f906e858a09759bdab888bd597b0

commit_message:
Modify keyring tests to test authentication

Currently keyring tests test the calls to the keyring service directly
and not their use in an actual authentication call. Modify them so we
test how the keyring performs under more realistic usage.

Change-Id: I2216dcaaa6464f39807fd79a3bea07d1de71f827

commit_message:
VMware: Fix ensure_vlan_bridge to work properly with existing DVS

With Nova Flat Network, if the DVS exists, we should not try to
worry about virtual switches or port groups. We should just return
the network_ref

ensure_vlan_bridge was also missing the return of network_ref at
tne end of the method, added that as well since that return value
is needed/used in virt/vmwareapi/vmops.py#L191

Fixes LP# 1194018

Change-Id: I78c71e4c15f1aa87378ae2eb0448c047c6a2a666

commit_message:
Fixes unexpected exception message in PciConfigInvalidWhitelist

When an exception PciConfigInvalidWhitelist occurs, the message "An
unknown exception occurred." was obtained. This is due to the content
of the variable not being overriden correctly. The same typo applies
to PciTrackerInvalidNodeId.

Closes-Bug: #1221493
Change-Id: I589cb8d0a1426eb84bbbc4a819b5585e4e746843

commit_message:
Ensure anti affinity scheduling works

The query for the group in the system_metadata would not correctly
filter the instances with the groups.

In addition to this change 4a03071db23196c4ac1ec0d8ea163c46887d3b08
ensured that the scheduling filter was only run once.
In cases when provisioning fails and rescheduling
takes place the filter must be invoked (if it is in the filter tool
chain).

Fixes bug: 1218878
Fixes bug: 1206502

Change-Id: I623c73635c36ffa038ae01476a25ba0c0863e536

extensions. Bundling them together to save on review load

commit_message:
Delete expired instance console auth tokens

Instance console auth tokens never get deleted from the cache
before the instnace is deleted, this is a waste of memory. now
we check if tokens are expired then remove them from the cache
before store new tokens.

Fix bug #1209134

Co-authored-by: Takashi Natsume <natsume.takashi@lab.ntt.co.jp>
(cherry picked from commit e3bbf2e81137bbcdc39bdfb4c4ff62f30c37afda)
Conflicts:
	nova/tests/consoleauth/test_consoleauth.py

Change-Id: I8dd5089ebaed3b3d91932f1f1558bbe302cd5675

commit_message:
Don't use ModelBase.save() inside of transaction

We using block 'with session.begin()' to organize some operations in
one transaction. session.begin() returns a transaction instance, then
does some operations, and will commit or rollback automatically
before leaving the block. ModelBase.save() always submit a commit,
and that is not expected.
When we get a persistent object from database, we just modify the
object inside of block 'with session.begin()' and sqlalchemy will
update it,don't need method session.add() or ModelBase.save()

Fixes bug #1224429

Change-Id: I8af3fd4b62a915833bf303b6892d432043fb57a9

@Lingxian Kong - the issue is that there are a lot of unnecessary calls to the pci driver code when the host does not report the pci stats.
This is a specific place where the database may be access - https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/compute/resource_tracker.py#L420
None of the self.pci_tracker should actually be called if the host does not require this.
I hope that this addresses your concern
Thanks
Gary'}, {'account_id': 6732, 'date': '2013-09-23 10:18:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: No score

@garyk:  
refering to https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/pci/pci_manager.py#L124, if PCI stats are not reported, should not the 'pci_devs' be empty list? If so, there will be no db changes. I wish I was at the right place.  
--kong"}, {'account_id': 4573, 'date': '2013-09-23 18:35:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Only update PCI stats if they are reported from the host

Not all drivers and hosts may report PCI stats. These should only
be updated if they are actually reported. This will save valuable cycles
and not have any unnecessary database access.

Fixes bug: 1228872

Change-Id: I3e0170638f3820422dbdea5dfb9e02b2de2ceacd

commit_message:
Fixes misuse of assertTrue in virt test scripts

Misuse of assertTrue in places where assertEqual should be used.

If assertTrue is used, the test will always pass
if the first argument's boolean cast is True.
The second argument passed to assertTrue() will be regarded
as the error message when the assertion fails.

Fixes bug #1220541

Change-Id: I63ec4f35ee1a2430a5f6b54e40108b2c4ce3d480

'}, {'account_id': 100, 'date': '2013-09-09 21:32:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Ugh, the logging one is a pain in the ass. Lots of code logs error when catching an exception. This will quickly turn into one big mess of workarounds for this damn eventlet bug.

I wish eventlet would just release a new version already. The bug in eventlet we're working around had a fix committed in April (although the bug fix has been around for 9 months now):

https://github.com/eventlet/eventlet/commit/0195326cbec83e5358d18f03f0189daff593dac3

Not to say that we shouldn't workaround this bug right now since we're close to a release, but maybe we should put some pressure upstream to release a new version that has the bug fix so we can remove all of these workarounds and not worry about all of the places we can lose the exception context."}, {'account_id': 475, 'date': '2013-09-09 21:43:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: No score

@Johannes ++

@Russell Good point. Played around with some different approaches, and they're all uglier than what you have here so I'm okay with this merging as is now.

Though I still like that 'annotation' aspect of using `save_and_reraise`, it will allow us to identify these workarounds when eventlet finally releases the fix.

If we're willing teach `save_and_reraise` new tricks, we could rewrite the code in a pretty clean way, like:

try:
    pass
except processutils.ProcessExecutionError as e:
    with excutils.save_and_reraise_exception():
        self.db.floating_ip_disassociate(context, floating_address)
        if "Cannot find device" in str(e):
            LOG.error(_('Interface %s not found'), interface)
            raise excutils.RaiseThisInstead(exception.NoFloatingIpInterface(interface=interface))

where `RaiseThisInstead` allows `save_and_reraise` to pass through certain, blessed exceptions, and use the original for all others.

commit_message:
Don't lose exception info

Using eventlet introduces some extra fun into exception handling.  After
catching an exception, it is required to save off the exception details
if you want to be able to re-raise it later after doing other operations
which may do a greenthread switch.  That's what this patch does.  It
saves off the original exception that we intend to re-raise later and
ensures that nothing stomps on it in the meantime.

A test case was also added to exercise this code path to make sure the
exception saving and re-raising worked as expected.

Change-Id: Ibf5f06a30839b93ece500ce7dbb714f6509f85af
Closes-bug: #1202177

commit_message:
Make nova CLI use term "server" where possible

nova client was using terms "server" and "instance" interchangeably
which was very confusing.

This patch uses "server" where possible without touching the API.

Note that there are actions (instance-action, instance-action-list) and
arguments (--instance-name, --num-instances, ...) with "instance" in their
name which can't be changed easily.

Closes bug 1156648

Change-Id: I0570aa1c4dc9ad1852af307a2a4896f16073a6ab

commit_message:
Update pbr usage

We've discovered that having versions in setup_requires leads to evil
and death. Also, the setup-hooks in setup.cfg are completely unnecessary
anymore.

Change-Id: I8878e635e0828bbddb81d9c6321a9f10ad3b89fe

commit_message:
print out git references for trees

in order to be sure we understand the environment that's running
in an upstream test, print out the git information for the tree.
This will hopefully address questions of "which commit of tempest"
is being used for particular tests.

Change-Id: Ief4e8a17fd75945f02982d2adf8625fe927d823d

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-09-22 16:05:08.000000000', 'message': 'Corrected several usage of keys() for Python 3

Under Python2 dict.keys() returns a list, under Python 3 it returns an
iterator. Some places assumed that if they called keys() then it was
safe to modify the dict in a loop. Corrected this by calling list().

Change-Id: I7638263f288dd20590bd751d09194a919b921545
'}]
commit_message:
Corrected several usage of keys() for Python 3

Under Python2 dict.keys() returns a list, under Python 3 it returns an
iterator. Some places assumed that if they called keys() then it was
safe to modify the dict in a loop. Corrected this by calling list().

Change-Id: I7638263f288dd20590bd751d09194a919b921545

commit_message:
py33: 'dict_keys' object does not support indexing

In python 3, dict.keys() is a class of 'dict_keys', it does not
support indexing.

Cast the dict to list to get the "first" value of dict, which is
compatible with python 2&3.

Closes-Bug: #1229005

Change-Id: I561b7ada9e5ad936659a657b3161a9b93a15a788

commit_message:
Object cleanups

1) Fix uses of hasattr(self, base.get_attrname()) to use self.obj_attr_is_set().
2) Remove an unused variable created by recent fix.
3) Use functools.wraps() on decorators so we get correct function names
in tracebacks.

Change-Id: I07aac43742894dad22231771083a94248d300711

commit_message:
Clean up a little cruft

OpenStack runs a git service now, so instead of linking to github URLs,
link to git.openstack.org.
Versions for pbr in setup.py actually wind up being an error (and a very
odd one) Remove them.
The setup hook in setup.cfg is no longer needed.

Change-Id: I8f48ac194e6c01e9bb06fa5df6f2b2bf28c01636

commit_message:
xenapi: fix pep8 violations in nova plugins

Removed plugins/xenserver from tox.ini excludes list, ran tox -e pep8, and
fixed violations.

Fixes: bug 1197893
Change-Id: I8e0116304b07d54c49a01202b3ce6d3426097bb4

commit_message:
Add filter for soft-deleted instances to periodic cleanup task

The periodic cleanup task added recently does a db query to get
instances in need of cleanup. The filters applied to the query
must have a filter to not include soft-deleted instances.

This fix adds the required filter and adds a test to verify the
correct behavior.

Change-Id: I0c5d7e317d1fdd4e1e618c1c38870e775a715eab
Closes-Bug: #1223345

Auto_config disk and resize up should be able to correctly handle when
the flavor specifies root_gb=0.

When you try to resize down to root_gb=0, it doesn't really make sense,
so throw a reasonable error message, instead of failing in the middle of
the resize calculations.

Fixes bug 1152268
Change-Id: Ib26170d7d563cc8fd664c3680fecc4ac04e57b04
"}]
commit_message:
xenapi: fix where root_gb=0 causes problems

Auto_config disk and resize up should be able to correctly handle when
the flavor specifies root_gb=0.

When you try to resize down to root_gb=0, it doesn't really make sense,
so throw a reasonable error message, instead of failing in the middle of
the resize calculations.

Fixes bug 1152268
Change-Id: Ib26170d7d563cc8fd664c3680fecc4ac04e57b04

commit_message:
Libvirt: volume driver set correct device type

Due to a typo, libvirt volume driver was assigning the device type
passed to the connect_volume method to the wrong attribute of the
LibvirtConfigGuestDisk class (non existing device_type which is
completely disregarded, instead of the expected source_device), which
caused the rendered XML to always have the device set to 'disk'. This
patch fixes that issue.

Also adds the 'lun' type to the list of supported device_types since it
is supported by libvirt but was missed in the previous refactoring.

Tests are added to prevent future regressions.

Closes-bug: #1223890

Change-Id: Iee160afcc23f762a752df1ca20372944d5100291

commit_message:
Don't fail if volume has no image metadata

In the same way that nova shouldn't fail when booting an instance if the
image has no metadata, when booting from a volume it should accept the
fact that it has no image_metadata and return an empty dict.

Fixes bug #1220814

Change-Id: Idc0ff2106415a0662e57021e918dc5c6bf9a9a92

[{'created': '2013-09-12 06:32:13.000000000', 'message': 'Fix V3 API server extension point exception propagation

Adds the propagate_map_exception parameter to extension
manager initialisation in the servers plugin so extension
points for the V3 API propagate exceptions rather than
supress them. The parameter was missing from some of the
extension point managers.

Also adds a missing V3 API personality test which exposed
the problem with exceptions not being correctly propagated.

Very minor spelling fix to one of the tests

Change-Id: I53fa680cfab9219442610a5dceeb35b150314f6f
Closes-Bug: 1224293
'}]
commit_message:
Fix V3 API server extension point exception propagation

Adds the propagate_map_exception parameter to extension
manager initialisation in the servers plugin so extension
points for the V3 API propagate exceptions rather than
supress them. The parameter was missing from some of the
extension point managers.

Also adds a missing V3 API personality test which exposed
the problem with exceptions not being correctly propagated.

Very minor spelling fix to one of the tests

Change-Id: I53fa680cfab9219442610a5dceeb35b150314f6f
Closes-Bug: 1224293

commit_message:
Refresh network info cache for secgroups

Before updating security group rules, we need to make sure that
the info cache is up-to-date. Without this source groups are not
updated properly. This was a regression introduced in commit
85aac04704350566d6b06aa7a3b99649946c672c which fixed a potential
DOS using source groups.

Fixes bug 1216720

Conflicts:
	nova/network/manager.py
	nova/tests/network/test_manager.py

Change-Id: I6b5115df53f2e159ea506ef966cd49cedd35f83d
(cherry picked from commit 8679b2c8e7f9fddc31a74ad00f6705bca00a762b)

Looks good.  We are running this in our prod env.  However, I'll let someone else in the community look this over and approve."}, {'account_id': 6530, 'date': '2013-09-17 18:29:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Do we expect this to live for a long time? This change potentially pulls in a whole bunch of things that are not really germane to neutron itself (ie. build-essential, etc).

Along same lines, this will be broken out of the gate for anything other than Ubuntu. I know its a pain, but if we bring this in, we should probably also put some sane default attributes for those operating systems as well.

Wondering if a better way to implement this is to break it out as its own recipe so that it can be easily removed some point later in time. But, again, that depends on whether we intend to keep it around.

Similarly, has a PPA been considered for pushing artifacts vs. source?  I always get a little weirded out by building on the converging host. That said, this does not look like the first place this is done in the neutron cookbook.

Ideally, I think we need a better way to decouple packages/sources of bits from their respective configuration. But this is not specific to neutron. I can think of a number of reasons for wanting something like this, as well as a few different ways it could be implemented.'}, {'account_id': 2340, 'date': '2013-09-18 07:28:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

FWIW I agree with Craig at least with regards to not building from source in the cookbook. Having a package for Ubuntu (in a PPA) would be a lot nicer. Extracting it to a different recipe would also work AFAIC.

OTOH I could just turn a blind eye to this as it does not affect distros other than Ubuntu. For SUSE we already have openvswitch 1.10 packaged in the Cloud repositories.'}, {'account_id': 26, 'date': '2013-09-19 22:37:55.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Would it make sense to break it out into an openstack-network-ovs cookbook so if you're not using OVS you don't bring in the dependencies? There's already a lot of recipes, but I agree with Ionut that a separate recipe would be cleaner."}, {'account_id': 161, 'date': '2013-09-20 20:10:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Thanks, everyone for the feedback.

I'll work on breaking it out into its own recipe. It should be noted, however, that the build packages are only brought in once you're in the "use_source_version" code path *and* are running Ubuntu precise:

45 if node['openstack']['network']['openvswitch']['use_source_version']
 46   if node['lsb'] && node['lsb']['codename'] == "precise"
 47     platform_options["quantum_openvswitch_build_packages"].each do |pkg|
 48       package pkg do
 49         action :install
 50       end
 51     end

I also agree that there are other/better ways of doing this (for instance allowing the user to specify their own repo). I'm not a fan of building on every machine when it can be avoided, however I felt to do it this way would give people who don't have the manpower or expertise to maintain their own builds and repos an "immediate" option if they so chose to use it.

But, I'm totally keen to pull this out and put it in its own recipe. I'll submit a new patch rev once those changes have been completed.

commit_message:
Allow building OVS from souce

The lastest version of OVS in Ubuntu 12.04 is
quite old (1.4). 1.9 is the new LTS supported
version and 1.11 is the newest head version.

Version 1.10/1.11 has many new features and
performance improvements, so there is a benefit
in being able to install it over the default 1.4
packages.

By default, nothing changes in this patch.
You must explicitly set
['openstack']['network']['openvswitch']['use_source_version']
to true in order to enable it.

Change-Id: I3779b6b73f3e2c0a56d3bed6bf3e3a4184649c24

commit_message:
Fix logging of failed baremetal commands.

Subprocess output is bytestrings, not unicode, so %r is the right
format to use.

Change-Id: Ia6cd0986d6970093c859775bb321ecea632e0264
Closes-Bug: #1223253

commit_message:
Fixes modules with wrong file mode bits

Modified file permission from 755 to 644.
Removed a redundant blank line to avoid merged errors in gerrit
which happens if no content has changed.

Partially fixes bug #1224226

Change-Id: I01695db4a0a55183046edad2069210243d7c5617

commit_message:
Fixes modules with wrong file mode bits in virt package

Modified file permission from 755 to 644.
Deleted a redundant log setup in /nova/virt/baremetal/driver.py to
avoid merged errors in gerrit which happens if no content has changed.

Partially fixes bug #1224226

Change-Id: I9db283c5b49c9f64e6ea52b8b0771d47c5fbbb83

commit_message:
Add Neutron port check for the creation of multiple instances

Exception is thrown if multiple instances are launched with a single
Neutron port. Remove one duplicated test case
"test_create_instance_with_security_group_enabled".

Fixed Bug 1193434.

Change-Id: Ie5d426db0e0785043833e4e7f9a16c9591bee743

commit_message:
proxy: mongodb storage driver

This patch adds a mongodb storage driver for marconi-proxy. This also
includes the test driver and a test configuration file.

Change-Id: Ia039df7b8c86af8b3ec51732ca4cd7b533437fff
Implements: blueprint placement-service

commit_message:
Clean up check for migration 213

Migration 213 for PCI device needs to check whether the pci_stats column
and the PCI device table exist or not after and before migration.

For pci_stats column check, interface assertColumnExists and
assertColumnNotExists could be used to simplify.

PS: remove an unnecessary word 'image_id' in models.py.

Change-Id: I7f1ba266523bca68c950bd76449324cece09393f

commit_message:
Remove unused exceptions

* nova/exception (ImageDownloadModuleLoadError):
Never referenced.
* nova/exception (ISERTargetNotFoundForVolume):
Never referenced.
* nova/exception (InstanceMetadataNotFound):
Unreferenced since commit 0d417fa73
* nova/exception (ISCSITargetNotFoundForVolume):
Unreferenced since commit 4123094b2

This commit removes them.

Change-Id: I224c6b1d711add12320ca8e89486257a6517a1c9
